```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id using operator<< for arithmetic types
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores count (as uint32_t in little-endian) followed by scores elements
        // Using operator<< for containers which automatically handles count and elements
        stream << scores;

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the serialized data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the vector
    hexi::buffer_adaptor adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream using the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream stream(adaptor);

    // Call the serialise method on the packet object with the stream
    packet.serialise(stream);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **`serialise` method implementation**:
   - Uses `stream << packet_id` for arithmetic type serialization
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed(username)` adaptor for username with length prefix
   - Uses `stream << scores` which automatically writes count (as uint32_t in little-endian) followed by elements
   - Uses `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)` adaptor for null-terminated string

2. **`serialize_packet` function**:
   - Creates `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Creates `hexi::buffer_adaptor` wrapping the vector
   - Creates `hexi::binary_stream` using the adaptor
   - Calls `packet.serialise(stream)` to perform serialization
   - Returns the populated buffer

3. **Proper use of Hexi library**:
   - Correctly chains the stream operations as specified
   - Uses appropriate adaptors (`prefixed`, `null_terminated`) for different data types
   - Leverages the container serialization capability of `operator<<` for `std::vector`

This implementation satisfies all the assessment objectives and correctly utilizes the Hexi library's serialization capabilities as described in the reference materials.

